Interview Questions
Q1. What is Encapsulation?

Answer

Wrapping data and methods into one class and protecting the data by making it private.

Q2. How do we achieve Encapsulation?
Make variables private.
Provide public Getter and Setter methods.
Q3. Why use private variables?

To prevent direct access and protect data.

Q4. Why use Getter?

To read data.

Q5. Why use Setter?

To update data safely.

Q6. Which access modifier is mostly used in encapsulation?
private




NOTE---Encapsulation vs Abstraction

Students often confuse these.

Encapsulation	     Abstraction
Hides data	         Hides implementation
Uses private variables	Uses abstract classes/interfaces
Achieved with Getter & Setter        	Achieved with abstract methods
